headline: Fair Isaac (NYSE:FICO) Shares Fall 14% Over Last Month
summary: Fair Isaac (NYSE:FICO) experienced a 14% decline in its share price over the last month amidst several key events. The company's recent removal from three Russell 1000 indices could have influenced this downward movement by impacting investor sentiment. Meanwhile, initiatives like the partnerships with MI New York and MeridianLink may underscore efforts to enhance market presence and product offerings, although these positive steps seemingly didn't offset the broader decline.
